Privacy Policy
Last Updated:
14 Mar 25
At Lennoxs, we are committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and share your personal information when you use our services. By using Lennoxs, you agree to the practices described in this policy.
1. Information We Collect
We collect the following personal information when you use Lennoxs:
Personal Identification Information:
First name, last name, e-mail, and phone number.
Address Information:
Your delivery address.
Location Information:
Your geographic location.
We do not collect any information automatically through cookies, logs, or similar technologies.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use the information we collect to:
Process Orders:
To fulfill and deliver your orders accurately.
Send Notifications:
To keep you informed about your orders and updates.
Improve Our Service:
To enhance the quality and functionality of our services.
Marketing and Advertising:
Your information may be used for marketing purposes, such as sending you promotional emails.
3. Information Sharing
We may share your information with the following third parties:
Payment Services:
To process payments through platforms like Square Up.
Analytics Services:
To analyze usage data and improve our services.
Please note that Lennoxs is an international platform that may share data with services located outside your country.
4. Security Measures
We implement several security measures to protect your information, including:
OAuth2 Authentication:
Ensuring secure access to your account.
Encryption:
Protecting your data during transmission.
SMS/Email Validation:
Verifying your identity.
Additional Security Mechanisms:
Including HTTPS with certification, request limits per user to prevent DDoS attacks, authenticity validation, and location range verification.
5. Data Retention
Your personal information is stored in our database as long as you maintain an account with us. Authentication tokens expire after 7 days of inactivity.
6. User Rights
You have the following rights regarding your personal information:
Access:
View the information we hold about you.
Edit:
Update your personal details.
Delete:
Remove your account and associated data.
These actions can be performed directly within the "Profile" section of our app or website.
7. Children's Privacy
Lennoxs is family-friendly and accessible to children. We take extra precautions to protect the privacy of children using our service.
8. Policy Updates
We will notify you via email if there are any changes to this Privacy Policy. Updates are infrequent, but we recommend checking this policy periodically.
9. Contact Information
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:
contact@lennoxs.app
.
10. Legal Basis for Processing
Our processing of your data is based on
consent
and
legitimate interest.
By using Lennoxs, you automatically consent to this policy.
11. Use of Third-Party Services
Lennoxs uses third-party services such as Google Maps for location services and Square Up for payment processing. These services have access only to specific data (location for Maps, credit card information for Square Up) and do not access other personal information.
12. Data Storage and Processing
Your data is stored and processed on AWS servers located outside your country of residence.